reviewText: These two movies are family movies.  I will say, I liked the first one better.  However, they are both enjoyable and great for children above ages 2-3.  Very small children may enjoy watching the Penguins but not understand the story.  I actual purchased this one for a young lady in her early twenties.
Love the 1st movie! Great music, good storyline/life lesson. The story of the second movie was so-so, but the music and dancing was great! would still purchase the product.
This has become my daughter's favorite movie. She is 2 1/2 and loves penguins. It was a great deal to get both movies. The first one is her favorite though.
Two great movies. Both have heart. Each character compemented the other perfectly. The comedy is enjoyable for both adults and children. Highly recommend!

It was nice to purchase a double blue-ray package of these movies.  My son loves the Happy Feet series, so it was very nice to find this two pack in blue-ray format for so cheap on Amazon.

The movies/disc includes special features like music videos, dance-alongs, and some other additional features/bonus stuff.

My grandmother was a tour guide at the penguin exhibit in Sea World Florida. She had been living her dream to work with and around penguins ever since she was a stand in for the Mrs Howell on "Gilligan's Island."
For her birthday, I purchased this movie in hopes that it would of been the perfect gift.
However, she did not have a blu-ray player, so I had to work a few extra shifts at Krystal (steamed square burgers on white rolls) to afford a used blu-ray player from the pawn shop.
After seeing the movie, she became physically sick. She ended up having to quite her job because she was no longer covered by their insurance with the hopes that Obamacare would take "care" of her.  Obamacare wasn't taking care of her so she moved to Italy for better health care.
Working in the nautical industry did not prepare her as much as she had hoped. After the all male freight ship crew discovered her "skills," she was quickly put to task keeping them happy. No one was ever quite sure what that entailed.
Unfortunately, the care was little more than a pain pill and she passed away on the way home from the public health clinic there.
This movie has broken our home by being the cause of my grandmother's death.
I ordered this for my sick grandmother who lives away from us and the DVD was in Italian.  I did not know this when I ordered it...had NO IDEA.  I have never had this happen on AMAZON.
